  if (slug === 'city-palace-full-day-tour') {
    return [
      { question: "What is included in the Udaipur full day sightseeing tour?", answer: "This comprehensive [Udaipur Full Day Sightseeing Tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour) includes a dedicated government-licensed historian guide with deep expertise in Mewar royal history and Rajput architectural traditions, a private air-conditioned vehicle with professional chauffeur for seamless all-day transit across the City of Lakes, and priority access assistance at major monuments. The immersive itinerary covers the colossal City Palace complex, the serene Lake Pichola boat ride, the Jagdish Temple, the Saheliyon-ki-Bari garden, the vintage car museum, and the atmospheric old city lanes of Udaipur's UNESCO-candidate heritage zone." },
      { question: "How long does the Udaipur full day tour take?", answer: "This deeply immersive exploration of the Venice of the East requires a rigorous 8 to 10-hour deployment to experience the full spectrum of Mewar royal heritage and lakeside beauty. We typically commence at 9:00 AM at the towering City Palace complex, transition to a boat ride on Lake Pichola, explore the Jagdish Temple and Saheliyon-ki-Bari, and conclude with sunset views from the atmospheric rooftop terraces overlooking the illuminated palace. This [full-day itinerary](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour) ensures physically sustainable pacing while maximizing cultural depth and photographic opportunities." },
      { question: "Is the City Palace museum fully covered?", answer: "Yes, the magnificent City Palace, the largest palace complex in Rajasthan, receives the most significant time allocation of approximately 2 to 2.5 hours within this [Udaipur sightseeing tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). Your high-authority guide navigates you through the labyrinthine succession of courtyards, balconies, towers, and rooms that were constructed over 400 years by 22 successive Mewar kings. Highlights include the peacock mosaics of Mor Chowk, the mirrored brilliance of Sheesh Mahal, the crystal gallery, and the panoramic rooftop terrace providing commanding views over Lake Pichola and the famous Lake Palace hotel floating in the center." },
      { question: "Is the Lake Pichola boat ride included?", answer: "Yes, a traditional boat ride on the iconic Lake Pichola is a core highlight of this [Udaipur full day tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). This serene 45-minute cruise provides breathtaking perspectives of the City Palace rising dramatically from the eastern shore, the ethereal Jag Mandir island palace, and the world-famous Taj Lake Palace hotel appearing to float on the water's surface. Your guide provides detailed commentary on the engineering marvel of this 14th-century artificial lake and the romantic royal legends associated with each island structure. Evening cruises during sunset offer particularly spectacular golden-hour photography conditions." },
      { question: "Is hotel pickup and drop-off included?", answer: "Yes, seamless door-to-door transportation is a standard inclusion in this [Udaipur sightseeing tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). Your designated air-conditioned luxury vehicle and professionally licensed chauffeur will collect you from any hotel, haveli, resort, or railway station within Udaipur city limits. The vehicle remains exclusively at your disposal throughout the entire extensive day, providing a climate-controlled sanctuary between monument explorations. At the conclusion of your tour, you are smoothly transported back to your accommodation or any preferred drop-off location including the airport or bus terminal for onward travel." },
      { question: "Is the Jagdish Temple included?", answer: "Yes, the stunning 17th-century Jagdish Temple is a key architectural highlight within this [Udaipur full day tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). This Indo-Aryan style Vishnu temple, located just steps from the City Palace entrance, features extraordinarily detailed carved stone panels depicting scenes from Hindu mythology, elephants, horsemen, and celestial dancers. Your guide explains the significance of the Garuda shrine, the intricately carved shikhara tower, and the temple's continuous role as an active place of worship for over 350 years. The temple provides a fascinating counterpoint to the secular palace architecture, demonstrating the intertwined nature of royal power and Hindu devotion in Mewar." },
      { question: "Is this tour suitable for families with children?", answer: "This private [Udaipur sightseeing tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour) is wonderfully suited for families because Udaipur's lakeside setting, palace stories, and boat rides naturally enchant younger audiences. Your guide transforms tales of heroic Mewar kings, underwater treasure vaults, and floating palaces into engaging narratives for children. The private vehicle provides comfortable rest intervals between sites. The Lake Pichola boat ride is a particular favorite, and the vintage car museum with its spectacular collection of royal automobiles captivates visitors of all ages. We flexibly modify the pace and content to match your family's energy levels." },
      { question: "Are monument entry tickets included?", answer: "To maintain absolute financial transparency, this [Udaipur tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour) covers your private vehicle, professional chauffeur, and expert historian guide, while monument entrance fees are handled separately to ensure uninflated government rates. The City Palace museum, Lake Pichola boat ride, and other site entries are purchased by your guide on your behalf, ensuring you pay the exact published rates without hidden markups. This transparent pricing structure allows you to choose which optional sites to include and maintains complete control over your total expenditure throughout the day." },
      { question: "Is Saheliyon-ki-Bari garden included?", answer: "Yes, the charming Saheliyon-ki-Bari, or Garden of the Maidens, is a delightful component of this [Udaipur full day tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). Built by Maharana Sangram Singh for 48 women attendants who accompanied his queen as part of her dowry, this intimate garden features ornamental fountains, lotus pools, marble elephants, and a small museum. Your guide explains how this serene retreat functioned as a private feminine sanctuary within the broader patriarchal royal framework, providing a deeply humanizing counterpoint to the masculine military narratives that dominate most Rajasthani palace tours." },
      { question: "Can we watch the sunset from a rooftop restaurant?", answer: "Absolutely, and we strongly recommend incorporating the legendary Udaipur sunset into this [full-day tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). Your guide coordinates the day's timeline to ensure you are positioned at one of the atmospheric lakeside rooftop terraces during the golden hour. Options include the famous Ambrai restaurant directly facing the City Palace, the elevated Upré at the Lake Pichola Hotel, or the intimate Savage Garden. Watching the reflected sunset illuminating the entire City Palace facade across the water is universally considered one of India's most spectacular visual experiences." },
      { question: "What is the best time of year to visit Udaipur?", answer: "The optimal window for this [Udaipur sightseeing tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour) spans October through March when daytime temperatures range from a comfortable 20°C to 30°C. November and February provide the most pleasant conditions for extensive outdoor exploration. Post-monsoon October offers the lakes at their fullest and most photogenic levels. Avoid mid-April through June when temperatures can exceed 42°C. The July through September monsoon period fills the lakes dramatically and creates lush green landscapes, though intermittent rain can occasionally disrupt outdoor plans and boat services may be temporarily suspended during heavy rainfall." },
      { question: "Is the vintage car museum included?", answer: "The Garden Hotel's vintage car museum, housing a spectacular collection of royal vehicles including Rolls Royces, Cadillacs, and Mercedes-Benzes used by the Mewar royal family, can be included as an optional highlight of this [Udaipur full day tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). This unique attraction showcases how the maharanas blended traditional royal pageantry with modern automotive luxury. Each vehicle has a fascinating provenance story connected to specific royal figures and historical events. Your guide integrates this visit seamlessly into the broader narrative of Mewar's transition from traditional royal governance to the modern democratic era." },
      { question: "What languages are available for the guide?", answer: "We maintain a specialized roster of multilingual government-licensed historian guides for this [Udaipur sightseeing tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). Beyond fluent English as our absolute baseline standard, we can deploy senior experts delivering the complex Mewar dynastic history, Rajput architectural narratives, and cultural commentary in Spanish, French, and German. The profound historical density of Udaipur's palaces and the intricate Mewar royal genealogy demand communication in your native tongue to ensure zero loss of critical detail. Specify your linguistic preference upon booking for guaranteed matching with an appropriate specialist." },
      { question: "Is lunch included in the tour?", answer: "This package intentionally excludes meals to provide complete dietary freedom across Udaipur's exceptional culinary landscape. Your [local expert guide](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour) serves as a culinary concierge, recommending premium lakeside restaurants, authentic Mewari cuisine establishments, and international dining options. Options range from the romantic Ambrai with its City Palace views to traditional vegetarian thali restaurants in the old city. We schedule a strategic dining interval between the morning palace exploration and the afternoon boat ride, ensuring proper rest and the opportunity to experience Udaipur's renowned hospitality." },
      { question: "What is the cancellation policy?", answer: "We execute a transparent cancellation framework for this [Udaipur Full Day Tour](/india/udaipur/city-palace-full-day-tour). Cancellations made more than 24 hours prior to the scheduled pickup time receive a complete 100% full refund with zero administrative friction or hidden processing fees. Within the 24-hour window, restrictions apply to fairly compensate our permanently dedicated chauffeurs and government-licensed historian guides who have been exclusively reserved for your itinerary. This straightforward policy structurally protects both your financial investment and our team's committed resources for your comprehensive City of Lakes exploration." }
    ];
  }
  if (slug === 'lake-pichola-full-day-tour') {
    return [
      { question: "What is included in this private Udaipur sightseeing tour?", answer: "This comprehensive [Udaipur Private Full-Day Sightseeing Tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour) includes a dedicated government-licensed historian guide specializing in Mewar royal heritage, a private air-conditioned vehicle with professional chauffeur for seamless all-day transit, and a traditional boat ride on the iconic Lake Pichola. The extensive itinerary covers the monumental City Palace complex, the lakeside Jagdish Temple, the Saheliyon-ki-Bari garden, the Fateh Sagar Lake promenade, and the atmospheric old city bazaars, delivering the complete architectural and cultural payload of India's most romantic city in a single expertly orchestrated day." },
      { question: "Is the Lake Pichola boat ride a highlight of this tour?", answer: "Absolutely. The signature boat cruise on Lake Pichola is the romantic centerpiece of this [Udaipur private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour). This serene 45 to 60-minute cruise provides the most spectacular perspectives of the City Palace rising dramatically from the eastern shore, the ethereal Jag Mandir island palace where Shah Jahan once sought refuge, and the world-famous Taj Lake Palace hotel appearing to float on the water's surface. Your guide provides rich historical commentary throughout the cruise, connecting each lakeside structure to the extraordinary 1,400-year lineage of the Mewar royal dynasty." },
      { question: "How long does the complete tour take?", answer: "This deeply immersive exploration of the Venice of the East requires a comprehensive 8 to 10-hour deployment to experience the full spectrum of Mewar heritage, lakeside beauty, and cultural traditions. The itinerary commences at 9:00 AM at the towering City Palace, transitions through the Jagdish Temple and old city lanes, includes the Lake Pichola boat cruise, explores the Saheliyon-ki-Bari garden and Fateh Sagar Lake, and concludes with sunset views from an atmospheric lakeside terrace. This [full-day itinerary](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour) ensures no monument is rushed while maintaining physically sustainable pacing." },
      { question: "Is the City Palace included in this tour?", answer: "Yes, the monumental City Palace complex, the largest palace in Rajasthan, is a core component of this [Udaipur private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour) receiving approximately 2 hours of dedicated exploration. Your guide navigates the labyrinthine succession of eleven individual palaces constructed over four centuries by successive Mewar kings. The peacock mosaics of Mor Chowk, the mirrored brilliance of Sheesh Mahal, and the panoramic rooftop terrace overlooking Lake Pichola and the floating Taj Lake Palace deliver an architectural experience of extraordinary depth that anchors the entire day's historical narrative." },
      { question: "Is hotel pickup and drop-off included?", answer: "Yes, comprehensive door-to-door transportation is a standard inclusion in this [Udaipur sightseeing tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour). Your designated air-conditioned vehicle and licensed chauffeur will collect you from any hotel, haveli, resort, or railway station within Udaipur city limits at your preferred start time. The vehicle remains exclusively at your disposal throughout the entire day, providing a comfortable climate-controlled sanctuary between monument explorations. At the conclusion of your extensive tour, you are smoothly transported back to your accommodation or any preferred drop-off point including the airport terminal." },
      { question: "Can we visit the Jag Mandir island?", answer: "Yes, the Jag Mandir island palace can be incorporated into your Lake Pichola boat cruise during this [Udaipur private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour). This stunning 17th-century island palace served as a refuge for Mughal Prince Khurram, later Emperor Shah Jahan, during his rebellion against his father Jahangir. Many historians believe the white marble dome and garden layout of Jag Mandir directly inspired Shah Jahan's design for the Taj Mahal. Your guide draws these profound architectural connections during the island exploration, adding extraordinary intellectual depth to what would otherwise be merely a scenic boat ride." },
      { question: "Is lunch included in the package?", answer: "This package intentionally excludes meals to preserve your complete dietary freedom across Udaipur's exceptional restaurant scene. Your dedicated [local expert guide](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour) serves as a culinary concierge, curating recommendations based on your specific preferences. Options range from the legendary lakeside Ambrai restaurant with direct City Palace panoramas, to authentic Mewari thali establishments in the atmospheric old city lanes, to premium heritage hotel restaurants. We strategically schedule a dining interval between the morning palace exploration and the afternoon boat cruise, ensuring proper rest." },
      { question: "Is the Saheliyon-ki-Bari garden included?", answer: "Yes, the enchanting Saheliyon-ki-Bari, the Garden of the Maidens, is a delightful component of this [Udaipur private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour). Built by Maharana Sangram Singh as a private retreat for 48 women who accompanied his queen as part of her royal dowry, this intimate garden features ornamental fountains, lotus pools, marble elephants, and a small museum showcasing Mewar heritage. Your guide explains how this serene sanctuary functioned as a feminine retreat within the broader patriarchal court structure, offering a deeply humanizing counterpoint to the military-focused narratives of most Rajasthani palace tours." },
      { question: "Is Fateh Sagar Lake included?", answer: "Yes, the scenic Fateh Sagar Lake, Udaipur's second major lake, is integrated into this [full-day private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour). This artificial lake offers a more tranquil, locally authentic experience compared to the tourist-heavy Lake Pichola shores. The lakeside promenade is a favorite among Udaipur residents for evening walks, and the Nehru Garden island in its center provides a charming green escape. Your guide explains the hydraulic engineering that connected Udaipur's lake system, demonstrating how the Mewar dynasty created a sophisticated water management infrastructure that sustained this desert city for centuries." },
      { question: "What is the best time of year to visit Udaipur?", answer: "The optimal window for this [Udaipur private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour) spans October through March when temperatures range from a comfortable 20°C to 28°C, making extensive outdoor exploration highly pleasant. Post-monsoon October is particularly spectacular because the lakes are at maximum capacity, creating the fullest, most photogenic water reflections of the palaces. Avoid April through June when extreme heat exceeding 42°C makes outdoor walking genuinely uncomfortable. The monsoon months of July through September dramatically fill the dry lake beds but intermittent heavy rainfall can temporarily suspend boat services." },
      { question: "What languages are available for the guide?", answer: "We maintain a specialized roster of multilingual government-licensed historian guides for this [Udaipur private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour). Beyond fluent English as our absolute baseline standard, we deploy senior experts who deliver the complex Mewar dynastic history, Rajput warrior traditions, and architectural commentary in Spanish, French, and German. Given the emotional depth of Udaipur's romantic heritage and the intricate royal genealogy spanning 1,400 years, having a guide who communicates seamlessly in your native tongue ensures complete absorption of every historical nuance and cultural insight without any translation barrier." },
      { question: "Is this tour suitable for couples and honeymoons?", answer: "Exceptionally so. Udaipur is universally celebrated as India's most romantic city, and this [private sightseeing tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour) is ideally structured for couples and honeymoon travelers. The sunset boat ride on Lake Pichola, the intimate palace courtyards, and the atmospheric rooftop dining terraces create a naturally romantic progression throughout the day. Your guide discreetly adjusts the narrative to emphasize the legendary love stories of the Mewar dynasty. We can additionally arrange private sunset boat charters, luxury lakeside dining, and access to heritage hotel terraces for an additional romantic enhancement." },
      { question: "Are monument entry tickets included?", answer: "To maintain absolute financial transparency, this [Udaipur private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour) covers your private vehicle, professional chauffeur, and expert historian guide, while monument entrance fees and boat ride charges are handled separately at government rates. This ensures zero hidden agency inflation. Your guide purchases all tickets on your behalf, navigating the ticketing counters efficiently and eliminating queue waiting time. This transparent pricing strategy gives you complete control over which optional sites to include in your day, maintaining budgetary flexibility throughout the comprehensive exploration." },
      { question: "Is this tour suitable for elderly visitors?", answer: "This [Udaipur private tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour) can be comfortably adapted for elderly travelers because the City of Lakes terrain is generally flatter than hilltop fort cities like Jaipur. The City Palace has some stairs but also elevator access for upper floors. The boat ride is completely seated and gentle. The Jagdish Temple involves a manageable flight of steps. Your private guide expertly manages the pace, extending rest breaks in shaded areas and utilizing the air-conditioned vehicle between sites. We recommend a modified itinerary that prioritizes the most accessible and rewarding sites while reducing total walking distances." },
      { question: "What is the cancellation policy?", answer: "We execute a transparent cancellation framework for this [Udaipur Private Sightseeing Tour](/india/udaipur/lake-pichola-full-day-tour). Cancellations made more than 24 hours prior to the scheduled pickup time receive a complete 100% full refund with zero administrative friction or hidden processing fees. Within the 24-hour window, restrictions apply to fairly compensate our permanently dedicated chauffeurs and government-licensed historian guides who have been exclusively reserved for your specific itinerary date. This straightforward policy structurally protects both your financial investment and our team's professional scheduling commitment for your comprehensive lakeside exploration." }
    ];
  }

  if (t.includes('delhi') && t.includes('agra') && t.includes('day trip')) {
    return [
      { question: "What time do we leave Delhi for a Taj Mahal day tour?", answer: "To maximize your day and experience the Taj Mahal at its most tranquil, we typically recommend a **3:00 AM or 4:00 AM departure** from Delhi. This early start allows you to reach Agra just as the gates open for sunrise, avoiding the heavy morning traffic on the Yamuna Expressway." },
      { question: "How long is the Delhi to Agra drive and is the expressway safe?", answer: "The drive from Delhi to Agra via the **Yamuna Expressway** typically takes between **3 to 3.5 hours**. This modern, 6-lane toll road is one of India's best highways, offering a smooth and safe journey. We include all toll taxes, parking, and fuel in your tour package." },
      { question: "Is a same-day Taj Mahal tour from Delhi actually worth it?", answer: "Absolutely—thanks to the ultra-fast Yamuna Expressway, a **same-day trip is the most popular way** to visit Agra. A well-structured itinerary easily covers the Taj Mahal, Agra Fort, and a relaxed 5-star lunch." }
    ];
  }

  // --- PHUKET TOUR FAQS ---

  if (slug === 'james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket') {
    return [
      { question: "What is included in the James Bond Island speedboat tour from Phuket?", answer: "The [James Bond Island speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) includes: hotel pickup and drop-off from major Phuket areas, a full-day speedboat to Phang Nga Bay, a visit to James Bond Island (Khao Phing Kan) and the iconic Ko Tapu needle rock, sea cave canoeing through at least one hong (hidden lagoon), Koh Panyee floating village stop with seafood lunch, life jackets, and a professional English-speaking guide. National park entrance fees (฿300/person) are included. The tour runs approximately 10 hours door to door." },
      { question: "What time does the James Bond Island tour depart and return?", answer: "The [James Bond Island tour from Phuket](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) operates on a full-day schedule. Hotel pickup begins at 7:00–7:30 AM from Phuket. The group boards the speedboat at Ao Po Grand Marina at approximately 9:00 AM and returns to the marina around 4:30–5:00 PM, with drop-off at your hotel by 6:00 PM. Early departure is essential — the sea cave canoeing (hong) section must be timed to low tide, which typically falls in the late morning. Tours that depart later miss the optimal tide window." },
      { question: "How long is the speedboat ride from Phuket to James Bond Island?", answer: "The speedboat journey from Ao Po Grand Marina to the first stop in Phang Nga Bay takes approximately 45–60 minutes. James Bond Island itself is reached after passing through several limestone karst formations, approximately 100 km from Phuket. The return journey is similar. Total time on the water between all stops is 6–7 hours. The bay is sheltered from ocean swell, so the ride is significantly calmer than open-sea crossings to Phi Phi." },
      { question: "What is sea cave canoeing and is it included?", answer: "Sea cave canoeing through **hongs** is the standout experience on this tour and is fully included. Hongs are collapsed limestone chambers — hidden lagoons accessible only through low-level openings in the cliff face. Your guide paddles you through a narrow, dark passage (sometimes requiring you to lie flat) before emerging into a completely enclosed sky-lit lagoon surrounded by 30–50 metre vertical walls. The experience is extraordinary and completely unlike anything available on a standard beach day. The [James Bond Island speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) times the hong canoeing precisely to low tide — the only window when the cave entrance is accessible." },
      { question: "Is this tour suitable for children?", answer: "Yes — the [James Bond Island tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) is one of the most child-friendly excursions from Phuket. Phang Nga Bay has calm, sheltered water with no ocean swell, and the speedboat ride is smooth. Children find the hong canoeing experience especially exciting. Most operators set a minimum age of 3–4 years old. Life jackets are mandatory for all passengers and are provided on board. Children must be able to sit still in a kayak and follow instructions during the cave passage. The Koh Panyee floating village is fascinating for all ages." },
      { question: "What is the national park entrance fee and is it included?", answer: "The Ao Phang Nga National Park entrance fee is **฿300 per foreign adult** and ฿150 per foreign child. This fee is included in the [James Bond Island speedboat tour price](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) — you do not pay separately at the gate. Park fees support conservation of the 400 sq km protected marine area, including the mangrove forests and limestone karst ecosystems. Thai nationals pay a reduced rate (฿30/฿15). Park staff collect fees at checkpoints in the bay." },
      { question: "Is lunch included in the James Bond Island tour?", answer: "Yes — a seafood lunch at **Koh Panyee floating village** is included in the [James Bond Island speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket). Koh Panyee is a stilted fishing community built over the water in Phang Nga Bay, and lunch here is genuinely excellent — fresh prawns, squid, and fish cooked to order on a platform over the sea. Bring cash (฿200–฿500) for additional drinks, desserts, or souvenirs beyond the included meal. Vegetarian options are available on request — inform the operator when booking." },
      { question: "What should I bring on the James Bond Island tour?", answer: "**Essential**: reef-safe mineral sunscreen (chemical sunscreens are banned at national parks and actively damage coral), swimwear, a waterproof phone case or GoPro, and cash (฿300–฿500 for extras at Koh Panyee). **Recommended**: motion sickness medication if you are prone (take 30 minutes before departure), a light layer for the air-conditioned speedboat cabin, and a wide-angle lens for the karst scenery. **Leave behind**: large bags, valuables, and drones (prohibited in national parks — ฿100,000 fine). Most boats have small dry storage." },
      { question: "What is the difference between this tour and a private Phang Nga Bay tour?", answer: "The group [James Bond Island speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) accommodates 20–40 people on a large speedboat and follows a fixed itinerary — excellent value and well-organised. A private charter gives your group the entire boat, flexible timing, longer stops at each location, and a more intimate hong canoeing experience. For groups of 6+, private charter pricing often becomes comparable to group rates per person. See our [private yacht charter options](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) for full-day exclusivity." },
      { question: "What is the cancellation policy for the James Bond Island tour?", answer: "Free cancellation is available up to 24 hours before your scheduled departure for a full refund. If the Thai Marine Department issues a navigation advisory or conditions are officially unsafe, the tour is rescheduled to the next available date at no cost, or a full refund is issued. The [James Bond Island tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) runs year-round, but Phang Nga Bay's sheltered geography means weather cancellations are rare compared to open-sea destinations. Book with confidence during all seasons." },
      { question: "How does the James Bond Island tour compare to a Phi Phi Islands day trip?", answer: "The [James Bond Island tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) and the [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) are Phuket's two flagship day trips, but they deliver fundamentally different experiences. James Bond Island focuses on dramatic limestone karsts, sea cave canoeing through hidden lagoons (hongs), and the cultural experience of Koh Panyee floating village — it is more scenic and cultural. Phi Phi focuses on beach beauty (Maya Bay), open-water snorkelling, and tropical island energy. Phang Nga Bay is calm and sheltered year-round; the Phi Phi crossing is on open sea and rougher during monsoon. Ideally, do both on separate days — they complement rather than overlap. See our full [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket) for planning." },
      { question: "Can I combine a James Bond Island visit with other Phuket attractions?", answer: "The James Bond Island tour is a full-day commitment (10 hours door-to-door), so combining it with other major activities on the same day is not practical. However, if you have multiple days in Phuket, a strong itinerary pairs this tour with: a [Phi Phi Islands day trip](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) on day two, a visit to [Big Buddha](/thailand/phuket/big-buddha-phuket) and [Phuket Old Town](/thailand/phuket/phuket-old-town) on a free morning, and [Wat Chalong](/thailand/phuket/wat-chalong) temple nearby. Our [Phuket 1-day itinerary](/thailand/phuket/phuket-1-day-itinerary) covers how to maximise a short stay, while the [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026) helps plan multi-day visits." },
      { question: "Is Phang Nga Bay worth visiting compared to other destinations in Thailand?", answer: "[Phang Nga Bay](/thailand/phuket/phang-nga-bay) is one of the most geologically extraordinary locations in Southeast Asia — over 40 vertical limestone karst towers rising from an emerald-green sea, hidden lagoons accessible only by kayak, and mangrove forests teeming with wildlife. It is categorically different from Thailand's beach destinations and is often ranked alongside Ha Long Bay in Vietnam as a must-see natural wonder. The [James Bond Island speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) is the most efficient way to experience the bay's highlights in a single day. If you are visiting Phuket for the first time, Phang Nga Bay should be at the top of your list — it cannot be replicated anywhere else in Thailand. For broader trip planning across Thailand, see our [Bangkok tours](/thailand/bangkok) for city experiences that pair well with Phuket's island adventures." },
      { question: "What is the best season to visit James Bond Island and Phang Nga Bay?", answer: "Phang Nga Bay is accessible and spectacular **year-round** thanks to its sheltered geography — surrounding islands and mainland headlands block ocean swell from all directions. The [James Bond Island tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) runs every day of the year except during extreme weather events. That said, **November to April** offers the most consistent conditions: clear skies, calm waters, and the best photography light. The dry season also provides optimal visibility inside the sea caves during hong canoeing. May to October (monsoon) brings occasional rain showers but the bay remains navigable — rainfall is typically brief and dramatic rather than all-day. Water temperature is a consistent 28–30°C year-round. For the most comprehensive seasonal planning advice, refer to our [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026)." },
      { question: "How do I get from Phuket to James Bond Island independently without a tour?", answer: "While theoretically possible, visiting James Bond Island independently is impractical for most visitors. You would need to arrange private transport to Ao Po Grand Marina or Surakul Pier, hire a longtail boat (฿2,500–฿4,000 for the day), negotiate the national park entry, and arrange your own canoeing guide for the hongs. The [James Bond Island speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) handles all logistics, costs less than independent arrangements, and includes a knowledgeable guide who times the hong visits to tidal windows. Independent travel makes more sense for experienced Thailand travellers who want to spend multiple days exploring Phang Nga Bay by kayak from a base on Koh Yao Noi. For most visitors, the organised [island hopping tours from Phuket](/thailand/phuket/phuket-island-hopping) offer the best value and experience." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling') {
    return [
      { question: "What is included in the Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour?", answer: "The [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) includes: hotel pickup and drop-off from major Phuket areas, a full-day speedboat to the Phi Phi archipelago, a visit to **Maya Bay** (the beach from the film *The Beach*), Pileh Lagoon, Bamboo Island snorkelling stop, a swimming stop at Monkey Beach, buffet lunch on Phi Phi Don, and professional English-speaking guide. Snorkelling equipment (mask, fins, life jacket) and national park entrance fees are included. Total duration is approximately 10 hours door to door." },
      { question: "Is Maya Bay open in 2026 and what are the visiting rules?", answer: "Yes — Maya Bay fully reopened in 2022 after a 4-year ecological closure and is accessible in 2026. Thai National Park authorities now enforce strict access rules to protect the recovering coral ecosystem: **no swimming inside the bay**, a maximum visitor limit (~300 people at any time), no boat anchoring (mooring buoys only), and access only between 10:00 AM and 4:00 PM. The coral has visibly recovered and blacktip reef sharks have returned. The [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) handles all park regulations automatically — you simply enjoy the bay." },
      { question: "How long is the boat ride from Phuket to Phi Phi Islands?", answer: "By speedboat, the journey from the departure marina in Phuket to the Phi Phi Islands takes approximately **45 minutes to 1 hour**. Slower longtail boats take 2.5–3 hours. The crossing is on the open Andaman Sea — conditions are calmer November–April (dry season) and can be rougher May–October (monsoon). The [Phi Phi speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) uses modern, life-jacket-equipped speedboats. If you are prone to motion sickness, take antihistamine-based medication 30 minutes before departure." },
      { question: "What snorkelling sites are covered on this Phi Phi tour?", answer: "The [Phi Phi Islands snorkelling tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) covers three main snorkelling areas: **Pileh Lagoon** (shallow, crystal-clear turquoise water inside a natural limestone enclosed lagoon — one of the most photogenic spots in the Andaman Sea), **Bamboo Island** (surrounding coral gardens with excellent marine biodiversity, including turtles and blacktip reef sharks), and **Monkey Beach** (a short swim with rocky reef section). Snorkelling equipment is provided. The tour guide identifies marine species at each site. Water visibility typically reaches 15–25 metres November–April." },
      { question: "What marine life will I see while snorkelling at Phi Phi?", answer: "The waters around Phi Phi Islands support extraordinary marine biodiversity. On the [Phi Phi Islands snorkelling tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) you can expect: clownfish (Nemo) in anemone at Bamboo Island, schools of parrotfish, surgeonfish, and angelfish, moray eels in coral crevices, hawksbill turtles (regular sightings), and blacktip reef sharks in shallow water at Bamboo Island — non-aggressive and frequently seen in 1–2 metres of water. Maya Bay's recovering coral is already showing young colonies re-establishing. GoPro or underwater camera highly recommended." },
      { question: "Is lunch included in the Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour?", answer: "Yes — a buffet lunch is included at a beachfront restaurant on **Phi Phi Don** island. The lunch stop is typically at 12:30–1:30 PM and includes rice, grilled fish, Thai curries, fresh fruit, and soft drinks. Vegetarian and dietary alternatives are available — inform the operator when booking. The lunch location is on the island's main beach, allowing time to walk the waterfront, buy drinks, or rent a kayak for free exploration during the lunch break." },
      { question: "Can non-swimmers join this Phi Phi Islands tour?", answer: "Yes — non-swimmers can participate in the [Phi Phi Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling). Life jackets are provided and mandatory in the water. Non-swimmers can observe coral and tropical fish while wearing a life jacket and floating on the surface at the snorkelling stops. The boat tour, Maya Bay visit, and Phi Phi Don lunch require no swimming. However, since this is primarily a snorkelling-focused tour, swimmers and snorkellers will gain significantly more from the experience. Non-swimmers who prefer a beach day over water activities should also consider the [4-Island Tour](/thailand/phuket) which has more beach time." },
      { question: "What time does the Phi Phi Islands tour depart and return?", answer: "The [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour from Phuket](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) follows a full-day schedule: hotel pickup 7:00–8:00 AM, speedboat departure at the marina ~8:30 AM, arrival at Phi Phi Leh (Maya Bay) ~9:45 AM, multiple island stops through the day, return departure from Phi Phi Don ~3:30–4:00 PM, back at Phuket marina ~5:00–5:30 PM, hotel drop-off by 6:30 PM. Early departure is critical — Maya Bay is most beautiful in morning light and least crowded before 11:00 AM." },
      { question: "What should I bring on the Phi Phi Islands snorkelling tour?", answer: "**Essential**: reef-safe mineral sunscreen (chemical sunscreens are banned in national parks — bring zinc oxide or titanium dioxide based), swimwear, waterproof phone case or GoPro for underwater photos, and a towel. **Recommended**: rash guard or UV shirt for extended snorkelling, motion sickness medication (take 30 minutes before departure if prone), cash ฿300–฿500 for drinks and extras on Phi Phi Don. **Leave behind**: drones (prohibited in national park — ฿100,000 fine), chemical sunscreen, and large valuables." },
      { question: "What is the cancellation policy for the Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour?", answer: "Free cancellation is available up to 24 hours before scheduled departure for a full refund. In the event of officially unsafe sea conditions or Thai Marine Department advisories, the [Phi Phi Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) is rescheduled to the next available date at no additional cost, or a complete refund is issued. During monsoon season (May–October), rough conditions occasionally cause cancellations — the tour operator will communicate at least 12 hours in advance. December–April has the most reliable weather with very rare cancellations." },
      { question: "How does the Phi Phi Islands tour compare to the James Bond Island tour?", answer: "These are Phuket's two essential day trips and they are completely different experiences. The [Phi Phi Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) is about iconic tropical beauty — Maya Bay's white sand, turquoise lagoons, world-class snorkelling, and beach stops. The [James Bond Island tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) is about dramatic karst scenery, sea cave canoeing through hidden lagoons, and the cultural floating village of Koh Panyee. Phi Phi is more active and water-focused; James Bond Island is more scenic and cultural. If you have two days, do both. If only one, choose Phi Phi for snorkelling and beaches, or James Bond for geological drama and unique canoeing. Our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket) compares all top activities." },
      { question: "Can I visit Phi Phi Islands on a private boat instead of a group tour?", answer: "Yes — the [private Phi Phi Islands yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay) offers the same destinations (Maya Bay, Pileh Lagoon, Bamboo Island) but with your own boat, flexible timing, and no shared passengers. Private charters are ideal for couples, families, or groups of 4+ who want to control the pace, spend longer at favourite stops, and access quieter bays. For even more flexibility including multiple island destinations, our [Phuket private yacht catamaran charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) offers 7 different vessels. The group speedboat tour remains the best value for solo travellers or couples on a budget." },
      { question: "What other activities can I combine with a Phi Phi Islands day trip?", answer: "The Phi Phi tour is a full-day commitment (10 hours), so combine it with other Phuket activities on separate days. A strong multi-day Phuket itinerary: Day 1 — [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling), Day 2 — [James Bond Island and Phang Nga Bay](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket), Day 3 — [Big Buddha](/thailand/phuket/big-buddha-phuket), [Wat Chalong](/thailand/phuket/wat-chalong), and [Phuket Old Town](/thailand/phuket/phuket-old-town) exploration. Our [Phuket 1-day itinerary](/thailand/phuket/phuket-1-day-itinerary) helps maximise limited time. For travellers continuing to other parts of Thailand, pair your Phuket island days with [Bangkok's cultural tours](/thailand/bangkok) for a complete Thailand experience." },
      { question: "Are the Phi Phi Islands part of a national park and what does that mean for visitors?", answer: "Yes — the [Phi Phi Islands](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands) are part of **Hat Noppharat Thara–Mu Ko Phi Phi National Park**, established in 1983. This protected status means: entrance fees are charged (included in the [Phi Phi tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) price), chemical sunscreens are banned (reef-safe mineral sunscreen only), drones are prohibited (฿100,000 fine), and Maya Bay has visitor caps (approximately 300 people at a time). The national park designation has been instrumental in the bay's ecological recovery since the 2018 closure — coral coverage has increased dramatically and blacktip reef sharks have returned. These regulations ensure the islands remain stunning for future visitors. Learn more about the island ecosystem in our [Phi Phi Islands guide](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands)." },
      { question: "Is the Phi Phi Islands tour worth it or overhyped?", answer: "The [Phi Phi Islands](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands) absolutely live up to the hype — provided you set expectations correctly. Maya Bay is genuinely one of the most beautiful beaches in the world, and Pileh Lagoon's turquoise water inside a natural limestone amphitheatre is jaw-dropping. The snorkelling at Bamboo Island rivals the best in Southeast Asia. What the hype sometimes misses: Phi Phi is popular, so Maya Bay has visitor caps and specific access windows. The [Phi Phi speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) departs early specifically to beat the midday rush. For a quieter alternative that still includes Phi Phi, the [Phi Phi Khai Islands combo tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) adds the less-visited Khai Island. Our comprehensive [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026) covers all island options with honest advice." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch') {
    return [
      { question: "What is included in the Phi Phi and Khai Islands tour?", answer: "The [Phi Phi and Khai Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) includes: hotel pickup and drop-off, a full-day speedboat covering both **Phi Phi Islands** (Maya Bay, Pileh Lagoon, Bamboo Island) and **Khai Island** (Khai Nok or Khai Nai), snorkelling equipment, buffet lunch with seafood and Thai dishes, and a professional English-speaking guide. National park entrance fees and life jackets are included. The combination of Phi Phi's dramatic scenery and Khai's calm, shallow snorkelling bay makes this the most comprehensive single-day island tour available from Phuket." },
      { question: "What is Khai Island and why should I visit it?", answer: "**Khai Island** (Koh Khai) refers to a group of three small islands — Khai Nok, Khai Nai, and Khai Nui — located approximately 15 km east of Phuket. Unlike Phi Phi, Khai's waters are extremely shallow (0.5–3 metres) and protected from all wind directions, making the snorkelling conditions almost always ideal. The coral gardens immediately off the beach support dense populations of clownfish, sea turtles, and reef fish. The beach is small but beautiful and far less crowded than Phi Phi Don. Adding Khai Island to a [Phi Phi tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) provides a peaceful contrast to Phi Phi's dramatic karst scenery." },
      { question: "How is this tour different from the standard Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour?", answer: "The [Phi Phi and Khai Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) adds **Khai Island** as an additional stop, providing extra snorkelling time in calm, shallow water that is especially good for beginners and children. Phi Phi covers the dramatic scenery (Maya Bay, Pileh Lagoon, cliffs), while Khai provides a relaxed beach and snorkelling experience. The full-day itinerary is slightly more packed than a Phi Phi-only tour, but both destinations are in the same general direction from Phuket, so no significant extra travel time is added. Lunch is served on board or at a beachside venue rather than on Phi Phi Don." },
      { question: "What snorkelling spots are covered on this tour?", answer: "The [Phi Phi and Khai Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) covers: **Pileh Lagoon** (Phi Phi Leh — enclosed turquoise lagoon with coral edges), **Bamboo Island** (Phi Phi's best coral reef with turtles and reef sharks), and **Khai Island** (extremely shallow, calm coral garden ideal for beginners with consistently good visibility year-round). Three distinct snorkelling environments in one day — from deep-water coral walls at Bamboo Island to the wading-depth reef at Khai. Equipment (mask, fins, life jacket) provided and briefing given before the first water entry." },
      { question: "Is the Phi Phi and Khai Islands tour suitable for beginners and non-swimmers?", answer: "Yes — this is one of the most beginner-friendly tours from Phuket. The addition of Khai Island is specifically excellent for non-swimmers and first-time snorkellers: the water is only 0.5–2 metres deep in many areas, so you can stand while wearing a mask. Life jackets are provided for all water activities. The [Phi Phi Khai tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) is particularly recommended for families with young children or those who have never snorkelled before — the calm, shallow environment removes anxiety and maximises the underwater experience." },
      { question: "Is lunch included and what is served?", answer: "Yes — a full buffet lunch is included in the [Phi Phi Khai Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch). The spread typically includes Thai staples: pad thai, green curry, grilled fish, stir-fried vegetables, jasmine rice, fresh fruit, and soft drinks. Lunch is usually served at a beachside venue. Vegetarian and allergen-sensitive options are available on request — specify when booking. The meal quality is consistently good and genuinely filling. Bring cash (฿200–฿300) if you would like to purchase extra drinks or snacks beyond the included items." },
      { question: "What is the boat like on this tour?", answer: "The [Phi Phi Khai Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) uses a modern fiberglass speedboat with seating for 20–30 passengers, a small covered cabin section for shade and wind protection on the return journey, a sound system, and onboard fresh water. Life jackets are stored on board and must be worn during all water activities. The boats are serviced regularly and meet Thai marine safety standards. Groups are typically 20–35 people — if you prefer a private boat for your group, see our [private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping)." },
      { question: "What time does the Phi Phi Khai Islands tour start and end?", answer: "Hotel pickup begins at 7:00–8:00 AM from Phuket hotels. The speedboat departs the marina at approximately 8:30 AM, with the first island stop (usually Phi Phi Leh / Maya Bay) reached by 9:45 AM. Multiple stops through the day — Phi Phi and Khai — bring you back to the Phuket marina by approximately 5:00–5:30 PM, with hotel drop-off by 7:00 PM. The early start is important to reach Maya Bay before peak crowds (which peak between 11:00 AM and 2:00 PM). Total tour duration: ~10 hours." },
      { question: "What should I pack for this island tour?", answer: "**Essential**: reef-safe mineral sunscreen (chemical sunscreens are banned at national parks — use zinc oxide or titanium dioxide), swimwear, waterproof case for phone, towel. **Recommended**: rash guard for extended snorkelling, motion sickness tablet (take 30 minutes before departure if prone), cash ฿300–฿500 for extras. **Useful**: GoPro or waterproof camera — the snorkelling at both Phi Phi and Khai is highly photogenic. **Avoid**: chemical sunscreen, drones (฿100,000 fine in national park), and large bags. Dry storage space on speedboats is limited." },
      { question: "What is the cancellation policy for the Phi Phi Khai Islands tour?", answer: "Free cancellation up to 24 hours before departure for a full refund. If sea conditions are officially unsafe or the Thai Marine Department issues a navigation advisory, the [Phi Phi Khai Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) is rescheduled or fully refunded. During the dry season (November–April), cancellations are very rare. Monsoon season (May–October) may bring occasional rough crossings — the operator monitors conditions daily and notifies guests 12+ hours in advance. Book with confidence as all operators maintain transparent weather policies." },
      { question: "How is the Phi Phi Khai tour different from the standard Phi Phi Islands tour?", answer: "The [Phi Phi Khai Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) adds **Khai Island** as a bonus stop, giving you two distinct snorkelling environments in one day. The standard [Phi Phi Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) focuses exclusively on the Phi Phi archipelago — Maya Bay, Pileh Lagoon, and Bamboo Island. Adding Khai gives you ultra-shallow, calm-water snorkelling (ideal for beginners and children) alongside Phi Phi's dramatic deep-water sites. The Khai stop is en route back to Phuket, so minimal extra travel time. Choose the Khai combo if your group includes nervous swimmers or young children; choose the standard Phi Phi tour if you want maximum time at each Phi Phi site. Both are covered in our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket)." },
      { question: "Can I visit Khai Island without going to Phi Phi?", answer: "Yes — Khai Island is only 20 minutes from Phuket by speedboat, making it accessible as a half-day trip. However, standalone Khai-only tours are less commonly offered than the combined [Phi Phi Khai tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch). For a custom itinerary that focuses on Khai and other nearby islands (Coral Island, Racha), our [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) lets you design the exact route. Khai's extreme proximity makes it an excellent choice for families or anyone with limited time who still wants a genuine island snorkelling experience. See our full [Phuket island hopping guide](/thailand/phuket/phuket-island-hopping) for all island options and distances." },
      { question: "What makes Khai Island special for snorkelling?", answer: "Khai Island's snorkelling is exceptional because of its **extremely shallow, protected reef** — coral gardens start in just 0.5 metres of water, meaning you can literally stand up while observing tropical fish, sea cucumbers, and clownfish in anemone. The island is shielded from wind in all directions, so water is almost always calm and visibility is consistently high. Unlike the open-water sites at [Phi Phi Islands](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands), Khai never has significant current or surge. This makes the [Phi Phi Khai tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) the single best option for first-time snorkellers, anxious swimmers, and young children. Experienced snorkellers will still appreciate the dense marine life concentration." },
      { question: "What is the best time of year for the Phi Phi and Khai Islands tour?", answer: "**November through April** (dry season) offers the best conditions for the [Phi Phi Khai Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch): calm seas, 20–30 metre snorkelling visibility, and reliable sunshine. December through February is peak season — book 2–3 days ahead. March–April remains excellent with slightly warmer water. During monsoon season (May–October), the Phi Phi crossing can be rougher, but Khai Island's sheltered position means it remains swimmable on most days. For comprehensive seasonal planning including all [Phuket tours](/thailand/phuket) and weather patterns, consult our [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026)." },
      { question: "How does this tour fit into a multi-day Phuket itinerary?", answer: "The [Phi Phi Khai Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) is a full-day excursion that pairs perfectly with other Phuket experiences on separate days. A recommended 3-day plan: **Day 1** — Phi Phi and Khai Islands (this tour), **Day 2** — [James Bond Island and Phang Nga Bay](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) for dramatic karst scenery and cave canoeing, **Day 3** — explore [Phuket Old Town](/thailand/phuket/phuket-old-town), visit [Big Buddha](/thailand/phuket/big-buddha-phuket), and see [Wat Chalong](/thailand/phuket/wat-chalong). This covers Phuket's marine highlights and cultural landmarks. Travellers continuing to other Thai cities can add [Bangkok tours](/thailand/bangkok) for a contrasting urban experience. Our [Phuket 1-day itinerary](/thailand/phuket/phuket-1-day-itinerary) helps if you have limited time." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay') {
    return [
      { question: "What is included in the private Phi Phi Islands yacht cruise?", answer: "The [private Phi Phi Islands yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay) includes: exclusive use of a private yacht for your group (2–12 people), a professional captain and crew, visits to **Maya Bay**, Pileh Lagoon, Bamboo Island, and Monkey Beach, full snorkelling equipment, fresh water, snacks, and drinks on board, hotel pickup and drop-off, and national park entrance fees. There are no shared passengers — the entire vessel is yours. The private format means itinerary timing, stop durations, and route sequencing can all be adjusted to your group's preferences." },
      { question: "How is the private yacht cruise different from the group speedboat tour?", answer: "The fundamental difference is exclusivity. On a group [Phi Phi speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling), you share a boat with 20–40 strangers and follow a fixed schedule. On the [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay), your group has the entire boat — you choose departure time, linger at Maya Bay as long as you wish, have the snorkelling sites to yourselves, and experience the islands at your own pace. Private also means the captain can access smaller, less-visited bays and coves that group tours never stop at. For couples, families, and groups of 4+, the private experience is dramatically superior." },
      { question: "What type of yacht is used and how many guests can it hold?", answer: "The [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay) operates on a premium sailing or motor yacht (typically 45–65 feet) with a spacious deck, shaded salon, and sun deck. The maximum capacity is 10–12 guests depending on the specific vessel assigned. Every charter is a genuine private experience — no strangers, no fixed group schedule. The yacht is fully equipped with life jackets, snorkelling gear, and safety equipment meeting Thai marine authority standards. Your captain has extensive local knowledge of Phi Phi's tides, currents, and the optimal timing for Maya Bay entry." },
      { question: "Can we customise the route and choose which islands we visit?", answer: "Absolutely — complete itinerary flexibility is the primary advantage of a [private Phi Phi yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay). The standard route covers Maya Bay, Pileh Lagoon, Bamboo Island, and Monkey Beach, but your captain can adjust timing, add extra stops at secluded coves (Loh Samah Bay, Viking Cave viewpoint, private beaches on Phi Phi Leh's eastern shore), or skip any location that doesn't interest you. If the group wants to spend 2 hours snorkelling at Bamboo Island rather than 45 minutes, that is entirely your choice. The yacht belongs to your group for the full duration." },
      { question: "Is hotel pickup from all Phuket areas included?", answer: "Hotel pickup and drop-off is included from most major Phuket hotel zones: Patong Beach, Kata Beach, Karon Beach, Bang Tao, Surin, Rawai, and Phuket Town. Your private vehicle collects the group at the hotel lobby at the agreed time and transfers you to the yacht departure pier. After the cruise, the vehicle returns the group directly to your hotel. For guests in remote locations or on nearby islands (Phi Phi Don, Koh Yao), coordinate pickup logistics with the operator when booking — alternative meeting points can usually be arranged." },
      { question: "Is the private Phi Phi yacht cruise suitable for non-swimmers?", answer: "Yes — non-swimmers can comfortably participate in the [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay). Life jackets are always available and non-swimmers can float on the surface with mask and life jacket to see coral and fish without deep-water exposure. The deck-based experience — watching the limestone cliffs of Maya Bay, having lunch at anchor, and enjoying the sail — is genuinely spectacular regardless of swimming ability. The private format also means the crew can give individual attention to nervous swimmers or first-time snorkellers." },
      { question: "What is the best time of year for the private Phi Phi yacht cruise?", answer: "The optimal season is **November through April** when the Andaman Sea is at its calmest, snorkelling visibility reaches 20–30 metres, and the turquoise water colours are at their most vivid. December–February is peak season — the most consistently perfect conditions but book 3–5 days in advance for the [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay). March–April is excellent with slightly warmer water. May–October (monsoon) brings variable conditions — the outer sea can be rough, but experienced captains manage safe routes on calmer days. Always ask about current sea conditions when booking in monsoon months." },
      { question: "Is food and drink included on the private yacht?", answer: "Fresh water, soft drinks, and light snacks (fruit, crackers, onboard provisions) are included in the [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay). Lunch varies by operator — some provide a full catered meal on board, others stop at a Phi Phi Don restaurant. Confirm the meal arrangement when booking. If you have dietary requirements, inform the operator in advance. You are welcome to bring your own drinks, wine, or preferred snacks on board. Most private charters have a small cooler on deck for personal beverages." },
      { question: "What should we bring on the private Phi Phi yacht cruise?", answer: "**Essential**: reef-safe mineral sunscreen (mandatory in national park waters), swimwear, GoPro or waterproof camera for underwater footage, and a light layer for the sea breeze. **Optional**: your own alcoholic drinks if desired (most charters allow BYO), a wide-angle lens for the cliffs, and motion sickness medication if prone (though yachts are generally smoother than speedboats). **Leave behind**: chemical sunscreen (coral-damaging, banned in national parks), drones without a permit, and large wheeled luggage — the marina has secure storage." },
      { question: "What is the cancellation policy for the private Phi Phi yacht cruise?", answer: "Free cancellation is available up to **48 hours** before the scheduled charter for a full refund. Private yacht charters require 48 hours notice rather than 24 hours because of the coordination involved in preparing the vessel and crew. In the event of Thai Marine Department weather advisories or officially unsafe conditions, the [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay) is rescheduled to your next available date or fully refunded. The operator will notify you at least 12 hours before departure if conditions require rescheduling." },
      { question: "Is a private yacht cruise worth the extra cost compared to a group Phi Phi tour?", answer: "The value depends on your group size and priorities. For **couples**, the [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay) is a premium romantic experience — genuinely unforgettable for honeymoons and anniversaries. For **groups of 6+**, the per-person cost approaches group tour pricing while delivering an incomparably better experience: your own schedule, longer stops, quieter bays, and no strangers. The group [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) remains excellent value for solo travellers and budget-conscious pairs. Both visit the same iconic locations — the difference is pace, privacy, and flexibility. Compare all options in our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket)." },
      { question: "Can we combine Phi Phi Islands with other destinations on a private yacht?", answer: "Yes — a private yacht gives you the freedom to create multi-destination itineraries not available on any group tour. Popular combinations: [Phi Phi Islands](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands) + Racha Islands (outstanding diving), Phi Phi + Khai Island (shallow snorkelling for kids), or Phi Phi + a secluded beach lunch on an uninhabited island. Your captain advises on feasible combinations based on distance and sea conditions. For even broader island exploration, our [Phuket private yacht catamaran charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) offers 7 different vessels including large catamarans for group island hopping. See our full [Phuket island hopping guide](/thailand/phuket/phuket-island-hopping) for all destination options." },
      { question: "What is Pileh Lagoon and why is it a highlight of the private Phi Phi cruise?", answer: "Pileh Lagoon is a natural enclosed lagoon on the eastern side of Phi Phi Leh island — vertical limestone cliffs surround a pool of luminous turquoise water that appears to glow from below. On the [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay), your captain can anchor inside the lagoon during quieter windows, giving your group the space to swim, snorkel, and photograph without the density of group tours. The private format means you can linger here — many guests consider Pileh Lagoon even more spectacular than Maya Bay. Learn more about the full [Phi Phi Islands](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands) ecosystem in our dedicated guide." },
      { question: "How far in advance should I book a private Phi Phi yacht charter?", answer: "During **peak season (December–March)**, book the [private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay) at least **5–7 days in advance** — premium vessels sell out quickly. During shoulder season (April–May, November) and monsoon (June–October), 2–3 days is usually sufficient. Last-minute bookings are sometimes possible but limit vessel choice. For special occasions (birthdays, proposals, honeymoons), book 2+ weeks ahead to secure your preferred yacht. The booking confirmation includes your specific vessel details, captain name, and pickup logistics. If your Phuket dates are flexible, our [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026) helps identify the optimal timing." },
      { question: "What other Phuket experiences complement a private Phi Phi yacht day?", answer: "A private Phi Phi cruise covers your marine and island bucket list — pair it with Phuket's land-based highlights on other days. Strong multi-day plan: **Day 1** — [Private Phi Phi yacht cruise](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-private-yacht-cruise-maya-bay), **Day 2** — [James Bond Island and Phang Nga Bay](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) for karst scenery and cave canoeing (completely different to Phi Phi), **Day 3** — Explore [Phuket Old Town](/thailand/phuket/phuket-old-town) Sino-Portuguese architecture, visit the 45-metre [Big Buddha](/thailand/phuket/big-buddha-phuket), and see [Wat Chalong](/thailand/phuket/wat-chalong) temple. For travellers combining Phuket with other destinations, our [Bangkok tours](/thailand/bangkok) offer a contrasting city cultural experience. See our [Phuket 1-day itinerary](/thailand/phuket/phuket-1-day-itinerary) for time-limited planning." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping') {
    return [
      { question: "What is included in the Phuket private yacht charter?", answer: "The [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) includes: exclusive use of your chosen yacht or catamaran for the day (7 options available), a professional captain and crew, your custom island hopping itinerary around the Andaman Sea, snorkelling equipment, life jackets, fresh water and soft drinks on board, lunch (details vary by vessel), and hotel pickup from major Phuket areas. National park entrance fees are additional if your route enters protected areas. With 7 boats available — from speedboats to luxury catamarans — there is an option for every group size and budget." },
      { question: "What boats are available and how do I choose the right one?", answer: "The [Phuket yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) offers **7 distinct boats**: options range from nimble speedboats (fastest, best for reaching distant islands like James Bond Island or Similan) to spacious sailing catamarans (most stable, best for large groups and leisurely island days) and luxury motor yachts (premium comfort, ideal for special occasions). The right choice depends on: (1) group size — speedboats suit 2–8 people, catamarans 8–20; (2) destination — speedboats cover more ground, catamarans are better for anchored relaxation; (3) comfort priority — catamarans have less motion sickness risk. The booking page shows full specs for each vessel." },
      { question: "Which islands can we visit on the private Phuket yacht charter?", answer: "With the [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping), your captain can take your group to virtually any island within a half-day's sailing radius. Popular destinations: **[Phi Phi Islands](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands)** (Maya Bay, Pileh Lagoon — 45 min speedboat), **[Phang Nga Bay](/thailand/phuket/phang-nga-bay)** (James Bond Island, sea caves — 1.5 hrs), **Racha Islands** (excellent diving — 30 min), **Khai Islands** (shallow snorkelling — 20 min), **Coral Island** (family-friendly — 20 min), and uninhabited private beaches. The captain advises on optimal combinations based on your interests, group size, and current sea conditions." },
      { question: "How many people can join the private yacht charter?", answer: "Capacity varies by vessel — the [Phuket yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) offers boats ranging from **4 to 20 guests**. Speedboats typically hold 4–10 people comfortably; sailing catamarans accommodate 8–20. The entire vessel is exclusively yours regardless of group size — there are no shared passengers. This makes private charter an excellent choice for: couples and honeymooners, families with children, friend groups of 4–12, and corporate incentive groups. For very large groups (20+), the operator can arrange multiple boats travelling together." },
      { question: "Can we fully customise our island hopping itinerary?", answer: "Yes — complete customisation is the defining feature of the [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping). You choose the islands, the time spent at each, the activities (snorkelling, swimming, anchored lunch, beach walks), and the departure time. The captain provides expert recommendations based on current conditions, tides (critical for sea cave access in Phang Nga), and your group's interests, but the final itinerary is yours. You can also combine destinations not covered by any group tour — for example, combining Phi Phi and Racha Islands, or creating a full [Phuket island hopping](/thailand/phuket/phuket-island-hopping) route that covers 4–5 different islands in one day." },
      { question: "Is hotel transfer included in the yacht charter?", answer: "Yes — hotel pickup and drop-off is included from major Phuket hotel zones for the [private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping). A private vehicle collects your group from the hotel lobby at the agreed departure time and transfers you to the marina. After the charter, the vehicle returns you to your hotel. For guests staying in Krabi, Khao Lak, or on nearby islands, discuss pickup logistics with the operator when booking — meeting directly at the marina is often the most efficient option and saves time." },
      { question: "What is the best time of year for the Phuket yacht charter?", answer: "**November through April** is the optimal season for the [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) — calm Andaman Sea, 20–30 metre snorkelling visibility, reliable sunshine, and the most stable conditions for reaching all destinations. December–February is peak season; book at least 3–5 days in advance. March–April remains excellent. May–October (monsoon) brings variable conditions — catamarans handle light monsoon swell better than speedboats, and Phang Nga Bay (sheltered) remains accessible on most monsoon days. The operator confirms conditions 24 hours in advance." },
      { question: "Is the private yacht charter suitable for families with children?", answer: "Yes — the [private Phuket yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) is ideal for families. The private format means the itinerary, pace, and activity choices revolve entirely around your family. Catamarans are the best vessel for families: maximum stability (minimal sea sickness), wide flat deck for children to move safely, shade areas, and ample space. Life jackets in children's sizes are provided. Popular family itineraries include Khai Islands (very shallow snorkelling, great for children), Phi Phi Islands (iconic scenery and accessible snorkelling), and Racha Yai (calm bay with excellent coral). The crew is experienced with children on board." },
      { question: "What should we bring on the private yacht charter?", answer: "**Essential**: reef-safe mineral sunscreen (mandatory for all national park waters — use zinc oxide or titanium dioxide), swimwear, waterproof camera or GoPro for the snorkelling and scenery, and cash if your route includes stops at villages or restaurants. **Optional**: your own drinks (wine, beer — most charters allow BYO), a wide-angle lens for the karst scenery, seasickness tablets if prone (catamarans are much smoother than speedboats). **Leave behind**: chemical sunscreen, drones without permits, and anything you cannot afford to get wet. The crew provides dry storage but space is limited on smaller vessels." },
      { question: "What is the cancellation policy for the private yacht charter?", answer: "Free cancellation is available up to **48 hours** before the scheduled departure for a full refund. Private yacht charters require 48 hours notice to allow for vessel and crew preparation. In the event of Thai Marine Department weather advisories or officially unsafe sea conditions, the [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) is rescheduled to your preferred alternative date at no cost, or a complete refund is issued. The operator monitors marine weather forecasts daily and communicates proactively. During peak season (December–March), rescheduling is rarely needed due to consistently excellent conditions." },
      { question: "What is the difference between a catamaran and a speedboat for island hopping?", answer: "**Catamarans** are twin-hulled vessels that offer maximum stability, spacious decks, shaded cabins, and virtually no rocking — ideal for families, large groups, and anyone prone to seasickness. They cruise at moderate speed and make the journey itself enjoyable. **Speedboats** are faster, reaching distant destinations like [Phi Phi Islands](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands) or [James Bond Island](/thailand/phuket/phang-nga-bay) in less time, but offer less comfort and more bouncing on waves. The [Phuket yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) offers both types so you can choose based on your group's priorities: speed vs. comfort, destination distance, and group size. Our [Phuket island hopping guide](/thailand/phuket/phuket-island-hopping) compares all vessel types in detail." },
      { question: "Can we use the private charter for a sunset cruise instead of island hopping?", answer: "Yes — the [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) is fully customisable, and sunset cruises along Phuket's coastline are one of the most popular requests. A typical sunset charter departs at 4:00–5:00 PM, cruises past Promthep Cape (Phuket's most famous viewpoint), and anchors offshore to watch the Andaman sunset. Catamarans are especially popular for sunset cruises — their flat decks provide 360-degree views. Bring your own champagne or wine (BYO is allowed on most vessels). For daytime activities to pair with an evening sunset cruise, explore [Phuket Old Town](/thailand/phuket/phuket-old-town) or visit [Big Buddha](/thailand/phuket/big-buddha-phuket) earlier in the day." },
      { question: "How does the private charter compare to group tours for value?", answer: "For **solo travellers and couples**, group tours like the [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) or [James Bond Island tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) offer significantly better per-person value. For **groups of 6+**, the [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) often approaches group-tour pricing per person while delivering a dramatically superior experience: exclusive boat, custom itinerary, flexible timing, and access to quieter spots. For groups of 10+, private charter becomes the clear winner on both value and experience. Our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket) compares all options to help you choose the right format for your group." },
      { question: "What destinations are best for a private charter from Phuket?", answer: "The most popular [Phuket yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) destinations by experience type: **Snorkelling** — Racha Islands (clearest water, best coral), Khai Islands (shallowest, most beginner-friendly), [Phi Phi Islands](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands) (most iconic). **Scenery** — [Phang Nga Bay](/thailand/phuket/phang-nga-bay) (limestone karsts, sea caves, James Bond Island). **Beaches** — Coral Island (family-friendly), Bamboo Island (pristine national park). **Adventure** — Similan Islands (requires a fast boat, world-class diving). Your captain will recommend the optimal route based on weather, tides, and your group's interests. Full destination details in our [Phuket island hopping guide](/thailand/phuket/phuket-island-hopping)." },
      { question: "Is the Phuket yacht charter suitable for special occasions?", answer: "Absolutely — the [Phuket private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) is one of the most popular ways to celebrate birthdays, proposals, honeymoons, and anniversaries in Phuket. The private setting on the Andaman Sea with limestone island backdrops creates an extraordinary atmosphere. For proposals, the captain can anchor at a secluded bay at sunset. For birthdays, bring decorations and a cake on board — the crew will help set up. Luxury catamarans with champagne service and onboard BBQ are the most requested vessels for special occasions. Book 2+ weeks in advance during peak season. For planning the perfect Phuket trip around your celebration, see our [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026)." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket') {
    return [
      { question: "Is the Elephant Beach Experience in Patong ethical?", answer: "The [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) follows ethical tourism guidelines — elephants are not ridden with howdahs (hard seats), are not chained during guest interactions, and roam in a semi-natural environment along the beach. Activities focus on **feeding, bathing, and walking alongside** the elephants rather than performance-based entertainment. The facility works with veterinarians who monitor elephant health and diet. While no captive-elephant experience can replicate full wild freedom, this programme prioritises animal welfare and educates visitors about elephant conservation in Thailand. Always look for operations that avoid bull-hooks, chains, and forced tricks." },
      { question: "What activities are included in the Elephant Beach Experience?", answer: "The [Elephant Beach Experience in Patong](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) includes **feeding elephants with bananas and sugarcane**, walking alongside them on the beach, bathing and swimming with the elephants in shallow water, and a professional photo session with your camera or phone. The experience typically lasts **60–90 minutes** depending on the package. You will learn about each elephant's name, personality, and rescue story from the mahout (handler). Some packages also include a short educational talk about Asian elephant conservation. This is a hands-on, interactive experience — not a show or circus performance." },
      { question: "Can you swim with the elephants at this Patong experience?", answer: "Yes — swimming and bathing with the elephants is one of the highlights of the [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket). The elephants wade into shallow, calm water along the beach while you splash, scrub, and play alongside them. The water depth is typically **waist-height for adults**, making it safe and comfortable even for non-swimmers. Mahouts supervise the entire bathing session to ensure both your safety and the elephants' comfort. Bring a waterproof camera or GoPro for stunning underwater footage. This is a genuinely unique Phuket activity — for more marine-based adventures, explore the [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling)." },
      { question: "What should I wear to the Elephant Beach Experience?", answer: "Wear **comfortable clothes you don't mind getting wet and muddy** — the bathing session means you will be splashed. Swimwear with a light cover-up is ideal. Wear closed-toe water shoes or sports sandals with heel straps (flip-flops can slip off in the mud). Avoid loose jewellery, dangling earrings, or anything an elephant trunk might grab. Bring a change of dry clothes, a towel, sunscreen, and insect repellent. The facility may provide basic changing areas. Leave valuables in your hotel safe or use the locker facilities if available." },
      { question: "Is the Elephant Beach Experience suitable for children?", answer: "Yes — the [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) is family-friendly and children as young as **3–4 years old** can participate with a parent or guardian alongside at all times. The elephants are accustomed to young visitors, and the mahouts are experienced in facilitating gentle, supervised interactions. Children particularly love the feeding sessions and water play. However, very young toddlers may be frightened by the elephants' size, so parental judgement is important. For families looking to combine activities, the [Phi Phi & Khai Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-khai-islands-speedboat-tour-with-lunch) is another excellent kid-friendly Phuket day trip." },
      { question: "Is hotel pickup included for the Elephant Beach Experience?", answer: "Yes — **complimentary hotel pickup and drop-off** is included from hotels in Patong, Karon, Kata, and surrounding areas for the [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket). The transfer vehicle collects you from your hotel lobby approximately **30 minutes before** your scheduled session time. For hotels outside the standard pickup zones (such as Mai Khao, Cape Panwa, or Rawai), a small additional transfer fee may apply — confirm with the operator when booking. The total time away from your hotel, including transfers, is typically **2–3 hours**, leaving plenty of time for other Phuket activities in the same day." },
      { question: "What is the best time of day to visit the Elephant Beach Experience?", answer: "The **morning sessions (8:00–10:00 AM)** are widely considered the best time for the [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket). Elephants are most active and playful in the cooler morning hours, the light is softer for photography, and the beach is less crowded. Afternoon sessions (1:00–3:00 PM) are also available but can be hotter, which means both you and the elephants may be less energetic. If visiting during Phuket's peak season (**November–April**), book at least **2–3 days in advance** as morning slots sell out quickly. Check our [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026) for seasonal planning." },
      { question: "How long does the Elephant Beach Experience last?", answer: "The hands-on elephant interaction lasts approximately **60–90 minutes**, depending on which package you book. The total time including hotel transfers is around **2–3 hours**. This includes the greeting and safety briefing (**10 minutes**), feeding session (**15–20 minutes**), walking with the elephants on the beach (**15–20 minutes**), bathing and swimming session (**20–30 minutes**), and photo time. The experience is unhurried and you are not rushed through any segment. Because it takes only half a day, many visitors combine it with an afternoon activity like a [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata)." },
      { question: "What tips should I know before visiting the Elephant Beach Experience?", answer: "**Top tips for the best experience**: (1) Avoid wearing red or bright orange — these colours can startle some elephants. (2) Move slowly and calmly around the animals; sudden movements can make them nervous. (3) Always approach from the side, never directly from behind. (4) Bring a waterproof phone case or GoPro — the bathing photos are the most memorable. (5) Do not use flash photography as it disturbs the elephants. (6) Apply reef-safe sunscreen before arrival, not chemical sprays near the animals. (7) Listen carefully to the mahout's instructions at all times. (8) The elephants love bananas — you can purchase extra bunches on-site for **฿50–100 ($1.50–3)**." },
      { question: "How does the Elephant Beach Experience compare to elephant sanctuaries in Chiang Mai?", answer: "Chiang Mai's elephant sanctuaries (such as Elephant Nature Park) are typically larger, more rural, and focus on full-day rescue-and-rehabilitation programmes with **no riding and no bathing** in newer ethical models. The [Elephant Beach Experience in Patong](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) is a shorter, more accessible format designed for travellers with limited time in Phuket — it offers **hands-on interaction including bathing** within a half-day schedule. Both prioritise no-riding policies and handler-supervised contact. The Phuket experience is ideal if your itinerary is packed with island tours like the [James Bond Island speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) and you want an elephant encounter without dedicating an entire day." },
      { question: "What other Phuket activities pair well with the Elephant Beach Experience?", answer: "Because the [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) takes only half a day, it pairs perfectly with an afternoon or evening activity. **Popular combinations**: morning elephants + afternoon [Seasoning Thai cooking class in Cherngtalay](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay), or morning elephants + evening [Muay Thai training class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners). For a full-day plan, do the elephant experience in the morning and take a sunset cruise on a [private yacht charter](/thailand/phuket/phuket-private-yacht-catamaran-charter-island-hopping) in the afternoon. Browse all options in our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket)." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay') {
    return [
      { question: "What dishes do you learn at the Seasoning Thai Cooking Class?", answer: "The [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class in Cherngtalay](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) teaches you to prepare **3–4 authentic Thai dishes** in a single session. The signature menu includes **Tom Yum Goong** (hot and sour prawn soup), **Pad Thai** (stir-fried rice noodles), and **Green Curry** with your choice of protein. Depending on the session, you may also prepare a Thai dessert such as mango sticky rice or coconut pandan pancakes. Each dish is made entirely from scratch using fresh market ingredients — no pre-made pastes or shortcuts. You eat everything you cook at the end of the class, which serves as a full meal." },
      { question: "Are ingredients and equipment provided at the cooking class?", answer: "Yes — **all ingredients, equipment, and cooking stations are fully provided** at the [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay). Each participant has their own individual cooking station with a wok, gas burner, utensils, cutting board, and all pre-measured fresh ingredients. The instructor demonstrates each step before you replicate it at your own station. An apron is provided to protect your clothes. You do not need to bring anything except an appetite and your camera — the open-air kitchen setting in Cherngtalay makes for excellent photos and videos of your cooking journey." },
      { question: "Can the cooking class accommodate dietary restrictions?", answer: "Yes — the [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) accommodates **vegetarian, vegan, gluten-free, and halal** dietary requirements with advance notice. Vegetarian and vegan versions substitute tofu or mushrooms for meat and use vegetable-based fish sauce alternatives. Gluten-free guests receive tamari instead of soy sauce and rice noodles are naturally gluten-free. Nut allergies are managed by omitting peanuts from Pad Thai. **Inform the operator at least 24 hours before your class** so the chef can prepare the correct ingredients. The instructor is experienced in adapting traditional recipes without losing authentic Thai flavour." },
      { question: "How long is the Seasoning Thai Cooking Class?", answer: "The [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) runs for approximately **3–4 hours** including the introduction, cooking, and eating. A typical session breakdown: **30 minutes** for welcome, ingredient introduction, and a walkthrough of Thai herbs and spices; **2–2.5 hours** of hands-on cooking (3–4 dishes prepared sequentially); and **30–45 minutes** for sitting down and enjoying everything you cooked. The pace is relaxed and social — this is not a rushed experience. If you are looking for a shorter or morning-only format, the [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) offers a morning jungle kitchen session." },
      { question: "Where exactly is the Seasoning Cooking Class in Cherngtalay?", answer: "The [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) is located in **Cherngtalay**, a residential area in northern Phuket approximately **15 minutes from Bangtao Beach** and **20 minutes from Surin Beach**. The kitchen is set in a charming open-air tropical setting surrounded by lush greenery — far more atmospheric than a hotel conference room. Cherngtalay is easily accessible from all major Phuket hotel zones. Hotel pickup is available from Patong, Karon, Kata, and northern beach areas. The exact address and Google Maps link are provided upon booking confirmation." },
      { question: "Do you get to take home recipes from the cooking class?", answer: "Yes — every participant at the [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) receives a **printed recipe booklet** with all the dishes taught during the session. The recipes include the exact ingredient measurements, step-by-step instructions, and the instructor's personal tips for replicating authentic Thai flavour at home. The booklet also lists common Western supermarket substitutes for hard-to-find Thai ingredients (such as galangal, kaffir lime leaves, and lemongrass). Many guests find this recipe booklet becomes a treasured souvenir — a practical reminder of your Phuket cooking adventure long after you return home." },
      { question: "Does the Seasoning Cooking Class include a market visit?", answer: "Some sessions of the [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) include an **optional local market tour** where the instructor guides you through a traditional Thai fresh market, explaining how to identify quality ingredients — from choosing the freshest galangal to selecting the correct type of chilli for each dish. The market visit adds approximately **30–45 minutes** to the experience. Confirm with the operator when booking whether your chosen session includes the market component. If a market tour is essential to your experience, the [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) includes a dedicated market tour as a core part of the morning programme." },
      { question: "How many people are in each cooking class?", answer: "The [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) operates with **small group sizes of 6–12 participants** maximum. This intimate format ensures the instructor can give personal attention to each guest, correct technique in real-time, and answer individual questions. Each participant has their own dedicated cooking station — you are not sharing a wok or burner with strangers. The small group also creates a warm, social atmosphere where you meet fellow food-loving travellers. For an even more private experience, enquire about private class bookings for couples or families." },
      { question: "Is the Seasoning Thai Cooking Class suitable for kids?", answer: "Yes — children aged **6 and above** can participate in the [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) with parental supervision. The instructor adjusts chilli levels for younger palates and involves kids in safe tasks like mixing, pounding curry paste with a mortar and pestle, and taste-testing. Children under 6 can accompany parents but may not have their own cooking station. Thai cooking is inherently fun and visual for children — the colours, aromas, and hands-on nature make it one of Phuket's best family activities. Pair it with the [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) for an unforgettable family day." },
      { question: "Are vegetarian and vegan options available at the cooking class?", answer: "Absolutely — the [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) fully supports **vegetarian and vegan** participants. Vegetarian versions of Tom Yum, Pad Thai, and Green Curry are prepared using tofu, vegetables, and mushrooms instead of meat or seafood. Vegan adaptations go further by replacing fish sauce with soy-based alternatives and omitting oyster sauce. The instructor explains how Thai cuisine traditionally uses plant-based flavour foundations (lemongrass, galangal, kaffir lime) that make vegetarian and vegan versions genuinely delicious rather than a compromise. Notify the operator at least **24 hours** before your class for ingredient preparation." },
      { question: "What other Phuket experiences complement the cooking class?", answer: "The [Seasoning Thai Cooking Class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) pairs beautifully with Phuket's other cultural and adventure activities. **Morning + afternoon plan**: take the cooking class in the morning, then join an afternoon [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) to burn off those calories. **Full cultural day**: combine the cooking class with a [Muay Thai training session](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) for the ultimate Thai cultural immersion. For travellers who want to try both Phuket cooking classes, the [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) offers a jungle kitchen setting with a market tour — a complementary but different experience. Plan your itinerary using our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket)." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata') {
    return [
      { question: "What makes the Kata jungle kitchen cooking class different from other Phuket classes?", answer: "The [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) stands out because of its **unique jungle kitchen setting** — you cook outdoors surrounded by tropical vegetation, herbs, and fruit trees in the hills above Kata Beach. Unlike hotel-based or indoor cooking schools, this open-air environment connects you with the ingredients growing around you. The class begins with a **guided market tour** at a local Kata wet market, giving you a full farm-to-table journey. This combination of market education + jungle atmosphere + hands-on cooking creates an immersive experience that goes far beyond following a recipe." },
      { question: "What is the market tour like before the cooking class?", answer: "The [Kata cooking class](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) begins with a **guided tour of a local Thai wet market** near Kata. Your instructor walks you through the stalls, explaining how to select fresh ingredients: choosing the most fragrant lemongrass, identifying the difference between Thai basil and holy basil, picking the best coconut milk, and understanding the dozens of chilli varieties. You will see and smell ingredients you may never have encountered — fresh galangal root, kaffir lime leaves, palm sugar, and fermented shrimp paste. The market tour lasts approximately **30–45 minutes** and sets the foundation for understanding Thai flavour profiles before you start cooking." },
      { question: "How many dishes do you cook at the Kata cooking class?", answer: "You prepare **4–5 dishes** during the [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata), which is slightly more than most Phuket cooking schools. The menu typically includes a **curry (green or red)**, a **stir-fry dish**, a **soup (Tom Yum or Tom Kha)**, a **noodle dish (Pad Thai)**, and sometimes a **Thai dessert**. Each dish is cooked individually at your own station, so you learn the complete process from ingredient preparation through to plating. The variety ensures you experience the key pillars of Thai cooking: hot, sour, sweet, and salty flavour balance. You eat everything you prepare as a full multi-course meal." },
      { question: "What time does the morning cooking class in Kata start?", answer: "The morning class at the [Kata jungle kitchen](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) starts at approximately **8:30–9:00 AM** with the market tour, and the full experience finishes around **1:00–1:30 PM**. Hotel pickup begins at approximately **8:00 AM** depending on your hotel location. The total duration is around **4–5 hours** including transfers, market visit, cooking, and eating. The morning slot is the most popular because the market is freshest early in the day, the jungle kitchen is cooler before midday heat, and you have the entire afternoon free for beach time or other activities like a [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket)." },
      { question: "Is hotel transfer included for the Kata cooking class?", answer: "Yes — **complimentary hotel pickup and drop-off** is included from hotels in Kata, Karon, Patong, and surrounding areas for the [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata). The driver collects you from your hotel lobby in the morning and returns you after the class. Hotels further north (Bangtao, Surin, Mai Khao) may incur a small additional transfer fee — confirm when booking. The total time away from your hotel is approximately **5 hours** including all transfers, market tour, cooking, and lunch. If you are staying near Cherngtalay, the [Seasoning Thai cooking class](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) is closer to your hotel." },
      { question: "How is the Kata cooking class different from the Cherngtalay Seasoning class?", answer: "Both are excellent, but they offer **different experiences**. The [Kata cooking class](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) features a **jungle kitchen setting**, includes a **local market tour**, teaches **4–5 dishes**, runs in the **morning**, and emphasises the full farm-to-table journey. The [Seasoning class in Cherngtalay](/thailand/phuket/seasoning-thai-cooking-class-phuket-cherngtalay) offers a more **polished, garden-kitchen environment**, focuses on **3–4 signature dishes** (Tom Yum, Pad Thai, Green Curry), and runs in both morning and afternoon sessions. Choose Kata if you value the market tour and rustic atmosphere; choose Cherngtalay if you prefer a refined setting closer to northern beaches. Many food enthusiasts do both for a complete Thai culinary education." },
      { question: "Are vegetarian and vegan options available at the Kata cooking class?", answer: "Yes — the [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) fully accommodates **vegetarian, vegan, and other dietary requirements** with advance notice of at least **24 hours**. The instructor substitutes tofu, mushrooms, and vegetables for meat, and uses soy-based alternatives to fish sauce and oyster sauce for vegan guests. The beauty of Thai cooking is that the aromatic base — lemongrass, galangal, chilli, garlic, kaffir lime — is naturally plant-based, so vegetarian versions retain authentic flavour. Gluten-free, nut-free, and halal accommodations are also available. Inform the operator when booking so ingredients are prepared correctly." },
      { question: "Do I need any cooking experience for the Kata cooking class?", answer: "**No cooking experience whatsoever is required** for the [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata). The class is designed for **complete beginners** and the instructor demonstrates every step — from slicing lemongrass to controlling wok temperature — before you replicate it at your own station. The pace is relaxed and patient, with the instructor circulating to help anyone who needs guidance. Experienced home cooks will also enjoy the class as it reveals authentic Thai techniques and ingredient knowledge that elevate home cooking significantly. The jungle kitchen atmosphere makes even seasoned chefs feel they are learning something genuinely new." },
      { question: "Do you receive a recipe booklet to take home?", answer: "Yes — every participant at the [Kata cooking class](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) receives a **printed recipe booklet** with complete instructions for all dishes taught during the session. The booklet includes ingredient lists with both Thai and Western names, step-by-step cooking instructions, the instructor's personal tips, and suggested substitutions for ingredients that may be hard to find outside Thailand (e.g., using regular basil as a partial substitute for Thai holy basil). The recipes are tested for home kitchen replication so you can recreate your Phuket cooking experience when you return home." },
      { question: "What should I bring to the Kata cooking class?", answer: "**Bring**: a camera or phone for photos and videos (the jungle kitchen is very photogenic), comfortable lightweight clothing that you do not mind getting splashed with sauce or oil, closed-toe shoes for the market tour (wet floors), mosquito repellent for the jungle setting, and a light appetite — you will eat a **full multi-course meal** of everything you cook. **Provided for you**: apron, all ingredients, all cooking equipment, drinking water, and recipe booklet. **Leave behind**: heavy bags, valuables, and sandals without heel straps (the jungle paths can be slippery). For more Phuket activity planning, see our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket)." },
      { question: "Is the Kata cooking class suitable for children?", answer: "Yes — children aged **5 and above** can participate in the [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) with parental supervision. The jungle setting adds excitement for kids, and the market tour is an educational adventure — seeing tropical fruits, live seafood, and exotic spices for the first time. The instructor adjusts spice levels for young palates and involves children in safe, age-appropriate tasks like pounding curry paste, mixing ingredients, and taste-testing. Kids under 5 can attend as observers for free. For families, combining the morning cooking class with an afternoon [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) creates an unforgettable full-day itinerary." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket') {
    return [
      { question: "What is the best season for surfing at Kata Beach in Phuket?", answer: "The best surfing season at Kata Beach is during the **southwest monsoon from May to October**, when consistent swells bring rideable waves of **1–3 feet** ideal for beginners and intermediates. **June to September** typically offers the most reliable surf conditions. During the dry season (November–April), Kata Beach is generally flat with minimal wave activity, making it unsuitable for surfing. The [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) operates during the monsoon season when conditions are optimal. Check our [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026) for month-by-month seasonal details." },
      { question: "Are Kata Beach waves suitable for beginner surfers?", answer: "Yes — Kata Beach is widely regarded as **Phuket's best beginner surf spot**. The waves during monsoon season are typically **gentle 1–3 foot swells** that break over a sandy bottom (no sharp reef or rocks in the main surf zone). The beach has a gradual slope, allowing beginners to stand in waist-deep water while practising pop-ups and catching whitewater waves. The [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) takes advantage of these forgiving conditions — your instructor selects the safest section of the beach based on that day's current and swell direction. Kata is to Phuket what Waikiki is to Hawaii: the perfect learner's wave." },
      { question: "How long is the private surf lesson at Kata Beach?", answer: "The [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) runs for approximately **1.5–2 hours**. This includes a **20–30 minute** land-based introduction covering board handling, paddling technique, pop-up mechanics, wave reading, and ocean safety, followed by **60–90 minutes** of in-water instruction. The private format means the entire session focuses exclusively on you — the instructor stays within arm's reach in the water, pushes you into waves, and provides real-time feedback on your stance and balance. Most beginners successfully stand up and ride a wave within the first hour of instruction." },
      { question: "Is all surfing equipment provided for the lesson?", answer: "Yes — **all equipment is fully provided** for the [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket). This includes a soft-top foam surfboard (the safest type for beginners — no hard fins or sharp edges), a surf rash guard to protect against board rash and sunburn, and a leash. Soft-top boards are **8–9 feet long**, providing maximum stability and buoyancy for learning. You do not need to bring any equipment — just wear swimwear, apply reef-safe sunscreen, and arrive ready to surf. The instructor selects the appropriate board size based on your height, weight, and experience level." },
      { question: "What are the age and fitness requirements for the private surf lesson?", answer: "The [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) is suitable for participants aged **7 to 65+**. No specific fitness level is required for beginners — if you can swim **25 metres unassisted** and are comfortable in waist-to-chest-deep water, you can learn to surf. The instructor adapts the lesson to your physical ability. Children aged 7–12 must be accompanied by a parent on the beach (not necessarily in the water). Surfing is less physically demanding than people expect for beginners — most of the effort is paddling and standing, not fighting massive waves. The gentle Kata Beach conditions make this accessible to virtually everyone." },
      { question: "What is the advantage of a private surf lesson versus a group lesson?", answer: "The [private surf lesson](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) provides **100% instructor attention** — compared to group lessons where an instructor divides time among 4–8 students, you receive continuous one-on-one coaching. This translates to **faster progression**: the instructor catches waves with you, physically adjusts your stance, and provides immediate feedback on every ride. Private lessons also allow complete schedule flexibility — you choose the time that suits the best wave conditions rather than fitting into a fixed group schedule. Most private students stand up on their first session; in group lessons, some students never stand up at all due to insufficient individual attention." },
      { question: "What is the best time of day for a surf lesson at Kata Beach?", answer: "The **early morning (7:00–9:00 AM)** and **late afternoon (3:30–5:30 PM)** are the best times for the [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket). Morning sessions benefit from calmer winds, fewer swimmers in the surf zone, and cooler temperatures. Late afternoon sessions often have the most consistent wave energy as afternoon sea breezes generate clean swell lines. **Midday (11:00 AM–2:00 PM)** is the least ideal — the tropical sun is intense, the beach is crowded, and onshore winds can chop up the waves. Your instructor will recommend the optimal time based on the day's specific surf forecast." },
      { question: "What should I bring to the surf lesson?", answer: "**Bring**: reef-safe mineral sunscreen (apply 30 minutes before the lesson and reapply after), swimwear, a towel, drinking water, and a waterproof camera if you want wave-riding footage. **Provided**: surfboard, rash guard, and leash. **Optional**: waterproof phone pouch (the instructor can take photos from the water), contact lenses instead of glasses (glasses cannot be worn while surfing), and a light snack for after the session. **Leave behind**: jewellery, watches, and sunglasses — anything loose will be lost in the surf. For other Kata Beach activities, the [Thai cooking class in the Kata jungle](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) pairs perfectly with a morning surf session." },
      { question: "Can complete beginners really learn to surf in one lesson?", answer: "Yes — **most complete beginners stand up and ride a wave** during their first [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket). The combination of Kata's gentle, forgiving waves, a stable foam surfboard, and one-on-one instruction creates ideal learning conditions. The instructor breaks surfing into manageable steps: first lying on the board, then practising the pop-up on the beach, then catching whitewater waves on your belly, and finally standing. Success rates for standing on the first lesson exceed **80%** in private format. Even if standing takes longer for some, every student rides waves on their belly — which is enormously fun in itself." },
      { question: "How safe is surfing at Kata Beach for beginners?", answer: "Kata Beach is one of the **safest surf spots in Thailand** for beginners. The wave break zone has a **sandy bottom** with no reef, rocks, or coral hazards. During the monsoon surf season, red-and-yellow flags mark the lifeguard-patrolled swim zone, and your [private surf instructor](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) operates within sight of the lifeguard station. The soft-top foam board eliminates the risk of hard-board injuries common with fibreglass shortboards. The instructor maintains physical proximity throughout the lesson and is trained in ocean rescue and first aid. Rip current awareness is covered in the safety briefing — Kata's rips are generally weak and predictable during the surf season." },
      { question: "What other Phuket activities complement a surf lesson?", answer: "A [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) takes only **2 hours**, leaving the rest of your day wide open. **Popular combinations**: morning surf + afternoon [scuba diving at Racha Yai Island](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island) (different day recommended for ear pressure), morning surf + afternoon [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) (the jungle kitchen is just minutes from the beach), or surf + evening [Muay Thai training class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) for the ultimate active Phuket day. Explore all adventure options in our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket)." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island') {
    return [
      { question: "Do I need a scuba diving certification to join this trip?", answer: "**No certification is required** for the [Phuket scuba diving trip at Racha Yai Island](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island). This is a **Discover Scuba Diving (DSD)** experience specifically designed for first-time divers with zero prior experience. Your PADI-certified instructor provides all theoretical and practical training on the day — including equipment use, underwater breathing, equalisation techniques, and hand signals. The DSD programme is an internationally recognised introductory format that allows you to dive under direct instructor supervision without holding any licence. It is the most popular way to try scuba diving worldwide." },
      { question: "How deep do beginner divers go at Racha Yai Island?", answer: "Beginner divers on the [Racha Yai Island dive trip](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island) descend to a maximum depth of **12 metres (40 feet)**, which is the PADI limit for Discover Scuba Diving participants. Your first dive typically reaches **6–8 metres** to build comfort and confidence, and the second dive may go to the full **10–12 metres** if you are comfortable. At these depths, the coral reefs and marine life at Racha Yai are spectacular — you do not need to go deep to see incredible underwater scenery. The water at Racha Yai is remarkably clear with visibility often reaching **15–25 metres**, making even shallow dives visually stunning." },
      { question: "What safety procedures are in place for beginner divers?", answer: "Safety is the top priority on the [Racha Yai beginner diving trip](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island). The instructor-to-student ratio is strictly **1:4 maximum** (often 1:2 for DSD divers), meaning your PADI instructor is always within arm's reach underwater. Before entering the water, you complete a **30–45 minute** confined water skills session practising breathing, mask clearing, and buoyancy control in shallow water. All equipment undergoes pre-dive safety checks. The dive boat carries emergency oxygen, a first-aid kit, and communication equipment. The Racha Yai dive sites are chosen for their calm, current-free conditions — specifically selected because they are the safest in the Phuket region for beginners." },
      { question: "What marine life will I see at Racha Yai Island?", answer: "Racha Yai Island is home to **diverse tropical marine life** that makes the [beginner diving experience](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island) genuinely spectacular. Commonly sighted species include: **clownfish** (Nemo) in their anemone homes, **parrotfish**, **triggerfish**, **moray eels**, **pufferfish**, **barracuda**, **blue-spotted stingrays**, and schools of **yellowtail fusiliers**. The hard and soft coral gardens at the dive sites are vibrant and well-preserved. Occasional sightings include **sea turtles** (especially green turtles), **reef sharks** (harmless bamboo sharks), and **giant groupers**. Visibility at Racha Yai is among the best near Phuket, so you will see marine life clearly even on your first dive." },
      { question: "How long is the boat ride to Racha Yai Island from Phuket?", answer: "The boat ride from Phuket's Chalong Pier to Racha Yai Island takes approximately **45–60 minutes** by dive boat. The vessel is a purpose-built dive boat with a covered deck, seating, toilet facilities, and a dive platform at the stern. The journey south through the Andaman Sea passes Coral Island and offers beautiful open-ocean views. During peak season (November–April), the sea is typically calm and the ride is comfortable. In monsoon season, the ride can be bumpier — if you are prone to motion sickness, take medication **30 minutes before departure**. For island experiences without diving, consider the [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling)." },
      { question: "How many dives are included in the full-day trip?", answer: "The [full-day Racha Yai diving trip](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island) includes **2 guided scuba dives** at different dive sites around Racha Yai Island. Each dive lasts approximately **30–45 minutes** depending on air consumption (beginners tend to use air faster). Between dives, you enjoy a **surface interval of 60–90 minutes** during which lunch is served on the boat and you can snorkel, swim, or relax on the deck. The two-dive format is ideal for beginners: the first dive builds foundational skills and comfort, and the second dive allows you to relax and truly enjoy the marine life with greater confidence and awareness." },
      { question: "Is all diving equipment provided?", answer: "Yes — **all scuba diving equipment is fully provided** for the [Racha Yai beginner dive trip](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island). This includes a BCD (buoyancy control device), regulator, wetsuit or rash guard, mask, fins, weight belt, and tank. The equipment is professionally maintained and inspected before every trip. The instructor ensures a correct fit for all gear before departure — mask fit is particularly important to prevent leaking. You do not need to bring any dive equipment. **Just bring**: swimwear, towel, sunscreen, and a change of dry clothes. Prescription mask inserts are available for guests with poor eyesight — request in advance." },
      { question: "Are there medical requirements for beginner scuba diving?", answer: "Yes — all participants must complete a **PADI medical questionnaire** before the [Racha Yai dive trip](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island). Certain medical conditions require a doctor's clearance letter before diving, including: **asthma, heart conditions, epilepsy, diabetes, ear/sinus conditions**, and pregnancy (pregnant women cannot dive). If you answer 'yes' to any medical questions, you must obtain a dive medical clearance from a doctor — this can be done at clinics in Phuket, but ideally arrange it before your trip. You must not dive within **24 hours of flying** afterwards, so schedule your dive at least one full day before any departure flights." },
      { question: "Can non-swimmers go scuba diving at Racha Yai?", answer: "The [Racha Yai beginner dive trip](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island) requires participants to be **comfortable in water** but does not require strong swimming ability. The PADI Discover Scuba programme does not include a swimming test. However, you must be able to float, put your face in water, and breathe through a regulator without panicking. Non-swimmers who are comfortable in water can participate — the instructor stays within arm's reach at all times, and the BCD (buoyancy vest) keeps you afloat on the surface. If you are a true non-swimmer who is not comfortable in water, consider snorkelling with a life jacket on a [Phi Phi Islands tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) as a first step." },
      { question: "What is the best season for diving visibility at Racha Yai?", answer: "The best diving visibility at Racha Yai Island is during the **dry season from November to April**, when visibility regularly reaches **20–30 metres** and water temperatures are a comfortable **28–30°C**. The [Racha Yai beginner dive trip](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island) operates year-round, but **January to March** offers the most consistently crystal-clear conditions. During monsoon season (May–October), visibility drops to **10–15 metres** and seas can be rougher, though Racha Yai is sheltered enough to remain diveable on most days. The dive operator monitors conditions daily and cancels trips only when safety requires it. For seasonal Phuket planning, see our [Phuket travel guide 2026](/thailand/phuket/phuket-travel-guide-2026)." },
      { question: "What other Phuket activities complement a scuba diving day?", answer: "The [Racha Yai dive trip](/thailand/phuket/phuket-scuba-diving-beginners-full-day-racha-yai-island) is a full-day activity, so plan it as a standalone day in your Phuket itinerary. **Excellent multi-day plan**: **Day 1** — Full-day scuba diving at Racha Yai, **Day 2** — [James Bond Island speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/james-bond-island-speedboat-tour-phuket) for above-water karst scenery (a perfect contrast to your underwater day), **Day 3** — [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) or [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) for a land-based cultural activity. **Important**: do not fly within **24 hours** of scuba diving due to decompression risk — schedule your dive at least one day before your departure flight. See all options in our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket)." }
    ];
  }

  if (slug === 'muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners') {
    return [
      { question: "What fitness level do I need for the Muay Thai beginner class?", answer: "**No specific fitness level is required** for the [Muay Thai training class in Phuket](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners). The class is structured for **complete beginners** with no prior martial arts or fitness training. The instructor adapts the intensity to each participant's ability — whether you are a regular gym-goer or someone who has not exercised in months. The session includes a warm-up to prepare your body, and rest breaks are taken whenever needed. You will be challenged but not overwhelmed. Many participants describe it as an intense but manageable workout that leaves them feeling accomplished rather than exhausted." },
      { question: "What Muay Thai techniques are taught in the beginner class?", answer: "The [Phuket Muay Thai beginner class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) covers the fundamental techniques of Thailand's national martial art. You learn the **basic stance and guard position**, **jab-cross-hook punch combinations**, **front and roundhouse kicks** (the signature Muay Thai weapon), **knee strikes**, **elbow strikes** (demonstrated on pads only), and **basic clinch work**. All techniques are practised on Thai pads held by the instructor or training partner — you never spar or hit another person in a beginner session. The instructor explains the cultural significance of each technique and how Muay Thai differs from Western boxing and kickboxing." },
      { question: "How long is the Muay Thai training session?", answer: "The [Muay Thai beginner class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) runs for approximately **1.5–2 hours**. A typical session structure: **15–20 minutes** warm-up (skipping rope, shadow boxing, stretching), **30–40 minutes** technique instruction (stance, punches, kicks), **30–40 minutes** pad work with the instructor (applying techniques in combinations), and **10–15 minutes** cool-down and stretching. The pace is controlled and includes water breaks. The total time commitment including arrival, changing, and post-session conversation with the trainer is approximately **2.5 hours**. This leaves plenty of time for other Phuket activities the same day." },
      { question: "What should I wear and bring to the Muay Thai class?", answer: "**Wear**: comfortable athletic clothing — shorts and a t-shirt or tank top are ideal. Many gyms provide Muay Thai shorts if you want the authentic look. Sports shoes are not needed as Muay Thai is practised **barefoot** on padded mats. **Bring**: a water bottle (essential — you will sweat heavily in Phuket's tropical climate), a towel, and a change of dry clothes. **Provided**: boxing gloves, hand wraps, Thai pads, and access to changing rooms and showers. **Optional**: bring your own hand wraps for hygiene if preferred (available for purchase at the gym for **฿200–300 / $6–9**). Apply sunscreen before arriving if the training area is partially outdoor." },
      { question: "Is the Muay Thai class safe for complete beginners?", answer: "Yes — the [Muay Thai beginner class in Phuket](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) is specifically designed to be **safe and non-contact** for first-timers. There is absolutely **no sparring** (fighting another person) in beginner sessions. All striking is done on padded Thai pads and heavy bags held by the instructor. The warm-up prepares your joints and muscles to prevent injury. The instructor corrects your form in real-time to ensure you are striking safely — improper wrist alignment on punches is the most common beginner mistake and is addressed immediately. Wrist wraps and gloves protect your hands and wrists throughout the session." },
      { question: "Can both men and women participate in the Muay Thai class?", answer: "Absolutely — the [Phuket Muay Thai class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) welcomes **all genders equally**. Muay Thai in Thailand has a long tradition of female fighters, and Phuket gyms are accustomed to training women at all levels. Many sessions have a roughly equal mix of male and female participants. The instructor adjusts intensity individually, not by gender — your session is tailored to your fitness and comfort level regardless of whether you are male or female. Female travellers often find Muay Thai to be one of the most empowering activities in Phuket. Pair it with a [private surf lesson at Kata Beach](/thailand/phuket/private-surf-lesson-kata-beach-phuket) for a full active day." },
      { question: "Is all training equipment provided at the gym?", answer: "Yes — the [Muay Thai beginner class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) provides **all necessary training equipment**: boxing gloves (various sizes), hand wraps, Thai pads, heavy bags, skipping ropes, and training mats. The gym has changing rooms, showers, and secure locker storage for your valuables. Some gyms also provide complimentary water and a post-training protein shake or snack. The equipment is sanitised regularly. If you are particular about hygiene, bring your own hand wraps (or purchase a fresh pair at the gym for **฿200–300 / $6–9**) — this is the only item that benefits from personal ownership." },
      { question: "Is this a real Muay Thai gym or a tourist experience?", answer: "The [Phuket Muay Thai class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) takes place at a **genuine Thai boxing gym** — not a hotel fitness centre or tourist show. You train alongside (or adjacent to) professional and semi-professional Thai fighters who use the same facility daily. The trainers are **experienced Thai fighters** with competition backgrounds, many holding regional or national titles. This authenticity is a significant part of the experience — the sounds, smells, and energy of a working Muay Thai gym cannot be replicated in a hotel setting. The beginner class is taught by fighters who are also skilled coaches, ensuring quality instruction within an authentic environment." },
      { question: "Can children participate in the Muay Thai beginner class?", answer: "Yes — children aged **8 and above** can participate in the [Muay Thai beginner class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) with parental consent. In Thailand, Muay Thai training often begins as young as age 5–6 for local children, so gyms are well-equipped to teach young participants safely. The instructor adapts techniques, intensity, and duration for younger students. Children typically love the pad work — hitting targets with gloves is engaging and confidence-building. Parents can observe from the gym's seating area or participate alongside their children. For families visiting Phuket, combining Muay Thai with the [Elephant Beach Experience](/thailand/phuket/elephant-beach-experience-patong-phuket) creates an action-packed day." },
      { question: "What is included in the Muay Thai class price?", answer: "The [Muay Thai beginner class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) price includes: **professional instruction** from a certified Thai boxing trainer, **all equipment** (gloves, wraps, pads), access to the gym's **changing rooms and showers**, and **drinking water**. Some packages also include hotel pickup and drop-off from Patong, Kata, Karon, and surrounding areas — confirm transfer inclusion when booking. National park fees or entrance tickets do not apply (it is a gym, not a tourist attraction). The session is a genuine training experience at a working Muay Thai gym with no hidden costs or upselling." },
      { question: "What other Phuket experiences pair well with Muay Thai training?", answer: "The [Muay Thai class](/thailand/phuket/muay-thai-training-class-phuket-beginners) takes approximately **2 hours**, making it easy to combine with other Phuket activities. **Best pairings**: morning Muay Thai + afternoon [Thai cooking class in Kata](/thailand/phuket/thai-cooking-class-phuket-kata) (burn calories then replenish with authentic Thai food), or morning Muay Thai + afternoon [Phi Phi Islands speedboat tour](/thailand/phuket/phi-phi-islands-speedboat-tour-maya-bay-snorkeling) (different day recommended for muscle recovery). For a full Thai cultural immersion day: **morning Muay Thai** + **afternoon cooking class** + **evening visit to Phuket Old Town**. Browse all Phuket adventure and culture options in our [Phuket things to do guide](/thailand/phuket/things-to-do-in-phuket)." }
    ];
  }

